<div class="row u-mb-4">
   <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h2>Form Components</h2>
    <p>We use a float label pattern for all text input fields, including text areas. If you must, you can get around this by using a class of <code>Input--noLabel</code>, though it's not recommended.</p>
    <h3>Text Inputs</h3>
    <p>By default, input fields occupy the full width of their parent container. For better usability, you can see the labels at all times via float labels.</p>
   </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-7">
  <div class="columns small-12">
    <div class="example">
      <input type="text" placeholder="Here is an input" class="u-mb-0" value="Test">
    </div>
    <pre>
      <code><%= display_code('
<input type="text" placeholder="Here is an input">') %></code>
    </pre>
  </div>
</div>

