<section>
  <div class="row u-mb-5">
     <div class="small-12 columns">
      <h3>Radios and Checkboxes</h3>
      <p>We've made checkboxes and radios work by hiding the input, and using a <code>span</code> tag to create an icon. We then position the label on top of the icon so we can simulate selecting and deselecting our checkboxes and radios.</p>
     </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row u-mb-4">
     <div class="small-12 columns">
      <h3>Checkboxes</h3>
      <p>Checkboxes are skinned, so a specific pattern must be followed. After the input, we must include an empty set of <code>span</code> tags and a label. All syntax is wrapped in a <code>.checkbox</code> to group them together.</p>
     </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row u-mb-7">
    <div class="small-12 columns">
      <div class="example">
        <div class="row u-mb-0">
          <div class="small-12 columns">
            <div class="checkbox">
              <input type='checkbox' name='chackbox' value='' id="checkbox" checked/>
              <span></span>
              <label for="checkbox">Option A</label>
            </div>
            <div class="checkbox">
              <input type='checkbox' name='chackbox' value='' id="checkboxB"/>
              <span></span>
              <label for="checkboxB">Option B</label>
            </div>
            <div class="checkbox">
              <input type='checkbox' name='checkbox' value='' id="checkboxC" disabled checked/>
              <span></span>
              <label for="checkboxC">Disabled</label>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <pre>
        <code><%= display_code('
<div class="checkbox">
  <input type="checkbox" name="checkbox" value="" id="checkbox" checked/>
  <span></span>
  <label for="checkbox">Option A</label>
</div>
<div class="checkbox">
  <input type="checkbox" name="checkboxB" value="" id="checkboxB"/>
  <span></span>
  <label for="checkboxB">Option B</label>
</div>
<div class="checkbox">
  <input type="checkbox" name="checkboxC" value="" id="checkboxC" disabled checked/>
  <span></span>
  <label for="checkboxC">Disabled</label>
</div>') %></code>
      </pre>
    </div>
  </div>


  <div class="row u-mb-4">
     <div class="small-12 columns">
      <h3>Radios</h3>
      <p>Radios work the same way as checkboxes but we wrap them in <code>.radio</code>.</p>
     </div>
  </div>


  <div class="row u-mb-7">
    <div class="small-12 columns">
      <div class="example">
        <div class="row u-mb-0">
          <div class="small-12 columns">
            <div class="radio">
              <input type='radio' name='radio1' value='' id="radioA" checked>
              <span></span>
              <label for="radioA">Option A</label>
            </div>
            <div class="radio">
              <input type='radio' name='radio1' value='' id="radioB"/>
              <span></span>
              <label for="radioB">Option B</label>
            </div>
            <div class="radio">
              <input type='radio' name='radio1' value='' id="radioC" disabled>
              <span></span>
              <label for="radioC">Disabled</label>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <pre>
        <code><%= display_code('
<div class="radio">
  <input type="radio" name="radio" value="" id="radio" checked>
  <span></span>
  <label for="radioA">Option A</label>
</div>
<div class="radio">
  <input type="radio" name="radio" value="" id="radioB"/>
  <span></span>
  <label for="radioB">Option B</label>
</div>
<div class="radio">
  <input type="radio" name="radio" value="" id="radioC" disabled>
  <span></span>
  <label for="radioC">Disabled</label>
</div>') %></code>
      </pre>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="row">
     <div class="small-12 columns u-mb-5">
      <h3>Select Menus</h3>
      <p>Native select menus must be enclosed in a <code>.Select</code> in order for the arrow to appear. Chosen select menus must include a class of <code>.chosen</code> and <code>.select</code>. There is a threshold set on the search input within the chosen select menu. If the menu includes less than 5 options, the search input will not be displayed.</p>
     </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row u-mb-7">
    <div class="small-6 columns">
      <h4>Native Select</h4>
      <div class="example">
        <div class="Select">
          <select class="u-mb-0">
            <option value="Apples">Apples</option>
            <option value="Mangos">Mangos</option>
            <option value="Pears">Pears</option>
            <option value="Plums">Plums</option>
            <option value="Nectarine">Nectarine</option>
          </select>
        </div>
      </div>
      <pre class="u-mb-4">
        <code><%= display_code('
<select class="select">
  <option value="Apples">Apples</option>
  <!--More options-->
</select>') %></code>
      </pre>
      <h4>Disabled Native Select</h4>
      <div class="example">
        <div class="Select">
          <select class="u-mb-0" disabled>
            <option value="Apples">Apples</option>
            <option value="Mangos">Mangos</option>
            <option value="Pears">Pears</option>
            <option value="Plums">Plums</option>
            <option value="Nectarine">Nectarine</option>
          </select>
        </div>
      </div>
      <pre>
        <code><%= display_code('
<select class="select" disabled>
  <option value="Apples">Apples</option>
  <!--More options-->
</select>') %></code>
      </pre>
    </div>

    <div class="small-6 columns">
      <h4>Chosen Select</h4>
      <div class="example">
        <select data-placeholder="Choose an Option" class="select chosen is-requiredSelect">
          <option value=""></option>
          <option value="Apples">Apples</option>
          <option value="Mangos">Mangos</option>
          <option value="Pears">Pears</option>
          <option value="Plums">Plums</option>
          <option value="Nectarine">Nectarine</option>
        </select>
      </div>
      <pre>
        <code><%= display_code('
<select data-placeholder="Choose an Option" class="select chosen">
  <option value=""></option>
  <option value="Apples">Apples</option>
  <option value="Mangos">Mangos</option>
  <option value="Pears">Pears</option>
  <option value="Plums">Plums</option>
  <option value="Nectarine">Nectarine</option>
</select> ') %></code>
      </pre>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

